==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Olio
<hw>O"li*o</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"l⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧ <it>or</it>
⟦omac⟧l"y⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>olla</ets> a round
earthen pot, a dish of boiled or stewed meat, fr. L. <ets>olla</ets> a
pot, dish. Cf. <er>Olla</er>, <er>Olla-podrida</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A dish of stewed meat of different kinds.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Besides a good <qex>olio</qex>, the dishes were trifling.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mixture; a medley.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A collection of miscellaneous
pieces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Olitory</ent>⟦br⟧
